<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: LOVE IN THE TIME OF CABLE TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Looking for that perfect negligee? Satin underpants? Massage oil? Cable 
television's next generation of home shopping is looking for you. 
</P>
<P>
 The fledgling Adam & Eve Channel and Cupid Network Television are selling sexy 
garments, books, videos, unguents, oils, games and toys. 
</P>
<P>
 Cupid's format is standard: ordering number, description, price, 800 number 
and credit card options appear on screen. Oh, and a live model or two. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's aiming at the married couple," said Offer Assis, Cupid president. "We 
think sex is nice, and the better you have sex at home, the more chance there 
is to keep your marriage alive. We are more conservative than Playboy. We'd 
rather be introduced as a 'love and romance' channel." 
</P>
</TEXT>
