<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RTC Accuses Newport Beach Developer of Overcharging: Three real estate 
companies owned by developer Donald Koll overcharged the government $648,961 
for managing an office building, according to a federal audit.Resolution Trust 
Corp. sent a letter to Koll demanding repayment after the audit showed that 
Koll affiliates improperly billed RTC for an executive recruiter, sports club 
memberships and bonuses, a spokeswoman said. A Koll Co. spokeswoman said the 
company had no comment. Among RTC's findings, the audit showed Koll Management 
Services charged $416,000 for personnel, $83,000 in office expenses and $14,000 
in other charges that the management fee should have covered. 
</P>
