<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; CITY OKS SHUTTING DUMP ON SUNDAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citing low patronage, the Simi Valley City Council has approved a plan to shut 
the city's landfill on most Sundays. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the plan -- recommended by staff from Ventura County and the cities of 
Simi Valley, Moorpark and Thousand Oaks -- the landfill would be open Mondays 
through Saturdays, and the third Sunday of each month. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the dump must be open two other Sundays each year under the 
agreement reached with landfill operator Waste Management. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan must receive final approval from the Board of Supervisors before 
going into effect. The board is scheduled to consider the matter in the next 
month. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
