<HEADLINE>
<P>
OKLAHOMA STATE DEFEATS FULLERTON ON BENZ'S THREE-RUN HOMER IN NINTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jake Benz hit a three-run homer against Ted Silva in the bottom of the ninth 
inning Sunday night to give Oklahoma State a 13-11 come-from-behind victory 
over Cal State Fullerton in the NCAA Midwest I Regional at Stillwater, Okla. 
</P>
<P>
 Benz's homer capped a five-run rally by the Cowboys. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton plays Memphis State today in an elimination game. The winner plays 
Oklahoma State tonight for the right to advance to Omaha for the College World 
Series. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton reliever Chad Rolish took an 11-8 lead into the ninth, but was 
replaced by Silva with one out and two runners on. Carl Grinstead doubled to 
left, driving in both runners, and Scott Doma walked. 
</P>
<P>
 Silva struck out Roberto Lopez before Benz hit his homer to right to end the 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Millan had three hits and drove in four runs for Fullerton. 
</P>
