<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; YOUNT SITS FOR CYCLE AS NUMBER'S 
RETIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robin Yount rode off into the right field bullpen on his new Harley-Davidson 
motorcycle after the Milwaukee Brewers retired his No. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Yount, who rode into County Stadium on a motorcycle during a post-World Series 
celebration in 1982, took one victory lap, then drove out of the stadium on the 
motorcycle given to him by the Brewers and Harley-Davidson Motorcycle Co. 
during a ceremony before Milwaukee's game against Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 Yount, 38, retired in February after 20 seasons in the major leagues, all in 
Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Florida Marlins placed reliever Bryan Harvey on the 15-day disabled list 
retroactive to May 26 because of a strained muscle in his left elbow and signed 
free agent infielder Mario Diaz. 
