<HEADLINE>
<P>
COTO DE CAZA'S BOOTH LEADS TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kellee Booth of Coto de Caza has a two-shot lead over Fullerton's Jenny Lee 
after the second round of the Girls' Junior Championships tournament, played on 
the 6,133-yard, par-72 El Conquistador Country Club Sunrise course in Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Booth shot a two-over 74 after shooting an opening-round 68.She had two-round 
total of 142. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee shot a 71 Sunday and is at 144. Jenny Glasgow of Corona del Mar (77-81) is 
at 158. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament concludes today. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Berry of Yorba Linda shot 76 in the second round of the ClubCorp Junior 
Championship, played on the 6,971-yard, par-72 Country Club's North Course in 
Akron, Ohio. His two-day total is 158. Michael Boyd of Tulsa, Okla., leads with 
a two-day total of 140. 
</P>
</TEXT>
