<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC IRVINE'S MAYEDA EARNS NCAA BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine hurdler David Mayeda will compete at the NCAA Track and Field 
Championships in Boise, Ida., the college announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayeda had posted a provisional qualifying time of 51.09 seconds in the 
400-meter intermediate hurdles in winning the Big West Conference title May 14. 
The automatic qualifying time is 50.70 but Mayeda's time was fast enough to 
make the 24-man field. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayeda, a junior from University High, will be the first Anteater to qualify 
for the NCAA meet since 1992. The 400 hurdle preliminaries are Wednesday. The 
final is Friday. 
</P>
