<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 IN 4 HOMELESS A VETERAN, STUDY SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One-fourth of the single homeless people in Britain have served in the armed 
forces, and defense cuts could send the numbers soaring higher, according to a 
charity's study. 
</P>
<P>
 In its study, the housing charity Crisis concluded that former servicemen are 
more disadvantaged than other homeless people because of the culture shock of 
leaving behind a regimented life. 
</P>
<P>
 The charity's director, Mark Scothern, predicted that the numbers would grow 
as the government's planned defense layoffs for up to 17,000 personnel are 
carried through. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
