<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. FESTIVITIES TO MARK MEMORIAL DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Memorial Day revelers can attend veterans' observances and a picnic in Orange 
County today. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton's festivities begin at 10 a.m. with the city's 56th annual Memorial 
Day Observance at Loma Vista Memorial Park, 701 E. Bastanchury Road. Offering a 
special salute to the Army Corps of Engineers will be Brig. Gen. Milton Hunter, 
commander and division engineer of the Corps' South Pacific Division. 
