<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISSING SCHIZOPHRENIC FOUND WITH RELATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old retarded and schizophrenic man who wandered away from a school 
for the developmentally disabled was found in his grandmother's care Saturday 
night, about 30 hours after he disappeared. 
</P>
<P>
 Police began searching for Willie Jonal Allen on Friday afternoon after he 
walked out of the Vista Day Treatment Center in the 14200 block of Roscoe 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Allen's disappearance prompted additional police patrols and door-to-door 
inquiries Saturday night. His caretakers were concerned because Allen did not 
have his medication to control bouts of schizophrenia and epilepsy. 
</P>
<P>
 Allen walked to the nearby home of his grandmother, who was unaware of the 
ongoing search. She took him to the Van Nuys Psychiatric Hospital for 
treatment, said Sgt. Jim Bilodeau of the Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was with his grandmother," Bilodeau said. "He was never in danger." 
DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
